mulberry (4.2.0a1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Version 4.2a1 — see CHANGELOG.md for full details
  * 64-bit portability (LP64): fix type sizes in offline cache, network
    protocol buffers, plugin interfaces, file format parsers, preferences
  * OpenSSL 1.1/3.x: migrate to opaque API, update dynamic loading,
    rewrite BIO CRLF filter, add version guards for all three generations
  * C++17 / GCC 13+: remove register keyword, auto_ptr, throw() specs,
    fix narrowing conversions, reserved identifiers
  * Fix connection drop leaving application permanently unusable;
    recover dead per-mailbox connections on demand
  * Fix UTF-16 BOM handling causing mojibake on Outlook/iOS messages
  * Fix format=flowed delsp buffer boundary bug, add delsp=yes generation
  * Fix bare CR rendering as spurious blank lines (RFC 5322 s4)
  * Fix preferences corruption causing 100% CPU on 64-bit
  * Fix offline cache corruption on 64-bit (unsigned long vs uint32_t)
  * Unicode clipboard copy/paste via UTF8_STRING selection
  * Compose key and dead key support (JX locale path fix)
  * Font menu: use fontconfig instead of XListFonts
  * xdg-open fallback for attachments and URL links
  * Accept bare mailto: URLs on command line
  * setlocale(LC_ALL, "") at startup (fixes 12-hour clock)
  * IMAP ID extension (RFC 2971)
  * User-Agent header on HTTP requests
  * Subject prefix stripping for multilingual Re:/Fwd: chains
  * Timezone database: build-time generation from IANA tzdata via vzic
  * Recovered 16 patches from original developer's SVN repository
  * Replace 3DES with AES-128-CBC for S/MIME encryption
  * Replace SHA-1 with SHA-256 for PGP signatures
  * Modernize internal keyring encryption from MD5+RC4 to Argon2id +
    XChaCha20-Poly1305 via libsodium; fix keyring file permissions
  * Replace MD5 with libsodium random bytes for Message-ID and MIME
    boundary generation; use BLAKE2b for POP3 UIDL hashing
  * Replace SHA-1 with SHA-256 for certificate fingerprints
  * Replace 3DES with AES-256-CBC for private key file encryption
  * Fix use-after-free in JX JString/JString16 insert and replace
  * Remove -fpermissive compiler flag (unnecessary since GCC 4.x era)
  * Static analysis fixes (cppcheck, clang-tidy, Infer, CodeQL, Coverity, GCC):
    use-after-free, null derefs, format strings, array delete mismatch,
    uninitialized variables, realloc leaks, double-scaled pointer math,
    23 allocation/deallocation mismatches, buffer over-read in JX
  * Removed bundled OpenSSL 0.9.8m (22MB)
  * Removed bundled PCRE 4.5 and GNU regex from JX, use system libs.
    JX's regex backend selector (regex.h) now includes system pcre.h
    directly, disabling the POSIX fallback path which relied on Henry
    Spencer's GNU extensions no longer provided by modern glibc
  * Removed obsolete lround() polyfill

  [ Debian Packaging ]
  * Updated to Standards-Version 4.7.0.0 (from 3.8.3)
  * Migrated to debhelper compatibility level 13 (from 7)
  * Rewrote debian/rules using modern dh sequencer
  * Build with full hardening flags (bindnow, PIE, RELRO,
    stack protector, FORTIFY_SOURCE, format security)
  * Added debian/copyright in DEP-5 machine-readable format
  * Added debian/source/format (3.0 native)
  * Added desktop entry and .install file
  * Added AppStream metadata (mulberry.metainfo.xml)
  * Added upstream/metadata with repository links
  * Added lintian overrides for upstream source artifacts
  * Added Homepage, Vcs-Git, and Vcs-Browser fields to control
  * Updated build-depends: libfontconfig1-dev, pkg-config, zlib1g-dev
  * Removed obsolete build-depends (libesd0-dev)
  * Fixed resource file permissions (chmod 644 after install)
  * Removed bundled OpenSSL build step, use system libssl-dev
  * Updated maintainer to reflect current maintenance

 -- yitzhaq <github@anonmail.uk>  Fri, 25 Apr 2026 03:00:00 +0200

